With a pawn on e4 Black can often agree to the e5-e4 advance. The major
difference is that the pawn on c5 controls firmly the d4 square. Therefore,
the manoeuvre Be3-d4 with the transfer of the knight to e3 is no longer a
problem for Black. Further-on, the extra space allows some additional
counter-attacking possibilities on the queenside.} 15. Be2 Bd7 16. Qd2 ({
