better thanks to his extra space and defended passer. In reality, it is the
difference in the working power of the bishops which is the dominant priority
in the position.} Rab8 26. Rdc1 Nd6 27. Bd3 (27. Nc4) 27... Re8 28. Rc2 (28.
Rc3 $1 {/\} Qd8 29. Rbc1 Be7 30. R1c2 {with approximately equal position.})
28... Qd8 29. Rbc1 Be7 $1 {Now we can appreciate the black bishop potential.
The lack of space is irrelevant as long as the beast can hop out on a working
